Hello STEAM Academy Parents and Families:

I hope that everyone is well. This post is an follow-up from the post sent last week about our transitions to a new learning platform. I apologize for any issues the transition has caused. Packets are still availabe and the work is also posted on our resources page for all grade levels. A Canvas schedule for the 3rd - 8th grade virtual classes has been emailed out to all parents. K-2 students will continue to use packets. Each teacher should be contacting you on a weekly basis. Please be patient and hopeful as we find our way through this change together. Please contact me if you have any issues, comments or need assistance.

Sincerely,

Jeff Spaletta

Interim Principal

Dear Students and Families,

On Monday, April 20th, Governor DeWine extended the closure of all Ohio schools through the end of the school year. The action was taken to contain the spread of the coronavirus (COVID-19). Now that this decision has been made, we are excited to announce our more permanent home learning plan platform (Canvas).

Until the end of the year, supplemental and teacher guided instruction will be provided through this online platform. Canvas will be replacing the weekly Choice Boards. A MODIFIED SCHEDULE will be rolled out on Thursday and Friday of this week. Each family should expect a call from teachers with student login information and schedule details. Students should login and enroll in the orientation course when they initially login.

Below is a link with specific instructions on how to access Canvas. Please let me know if you need any assistance.

INSTRUCTIONS TO LOGIN TO CANVAS HAVE BEEN SENT TO PARENT EMAILS.

Respectfully,

Jeff Spaletta

Interim Principal

post_text:
Hello to our STEAM Academy Families,

We are facing an unprecedented situation and we need to do everything in our power to slow the spread of COVID-19. At this point school is closed through April 5th, but everyone should be planning for the long run. Our target date for students to return is April 6th. We hope that you and your family are doing well.

Packets of student work through the extended break were given out. Besides the packets, student can log into the Exact Path program at login.edmentum.com. Teachers will be calling to check-in and provide any necessary assistance with the work.

The following resources were emailed to all families:

Free Wi-Fi through Charter Communication

Fun ways to learn from home

Edmentum worksheet bundles

Candy bar fundraising money was due on the 20th. For those that have turned in all re-enrollment paperwork, including proof of residency (POR) forms, there will be a drawing for two individuals to receive a 32-inch television. The drawing will be held on March 30th.

Warm regards,

STEAM Administration Team
text:
Hello to our STEAM Academy Families,

We are facing an unprecedented situation and we need to do everything in our power to slow the spread of COVID-19. At this point school is closed through April 5th, but everyone should be planning for the long run. Our target date for students to return is April 6th. We hope that you and your family are doing well.

Packets of student work through the extended break were given out. Besides the packets, student can log into the Exact Path program at login.edmentum.com. Teachers will be calling to check-in and provide any necessary assistance with the work.

The following resources were emailed to all families:

Free Wi-Fi through Charter Communication

Fun ways to learn from home

Edmentum worksheet bundles

Candy bar fundraising money was due on the 20th. For those that have turned in all re-enrollment paperwork, including proof of residency (POR) forms, there will be a drawing for two individuals to receive a 32-inch television. The drawing will be held on March 30th.

Warm regards,

STEAM Administration Team

post_text:
Sales Tax Holiday
Beginning in 2019, Sub. S.B. 226 provides for a permanent sales tax holiday on the first Friday, Saturday, and Sunday of August each year. For 2019, the sales tax holiday will begin on Friday, August 2 at 12:00 a.m. and end on Sunday, August 4 at 11:59 p.m.

During the holiday, the following items are exempt from sales and use tax:

Clothing priced at $75 per item or less;
School supplies priced at $20 per item or less; and
School instructional material priced at $20 per item or less.
